     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">The southern Brisbane suburb that young professionals and investors pursue for its proximity to the tech and business park precinct, motorway access, and a strong rental market that reflects genuine employment demand.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Eight Mile Plains sits approximately fifteen kilometres south of the Brisbane CBD, positioned at the intersection of the Pacific Motorway and the Logan Motorway in Brisbane's southern corridor. The suburb is defined by its proximity to a significant concentration of technology and professional services businesses, its exceptional motorway access, and its strong rental demand from professionals employed in the business parks that define the suburb's character and its appeal to investors. The buyer who targets Eight Mile Plains in 2026 has typically made a deliberate calculation about commuter efficiency and investment yield, and understands that this suburb offers a practical advantage that more lifestyle-oriented southern addresses do not.
    </p>
