    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The motorway interchange at Eight Mile Plains provides access that few southern Brisbane suburbs can match. The Pacific Motorway connects directly to the CBD and the Gold Coast, while the Logan Motorway provides access to Brisbane Airport and the western suburbs. For buyers and tenants whose work takes them across Brisbane, or who travel frequently, this access is a genuine practical asset that shows up in both buying decisions and rental demand. Garden City shopping centre in neighbouring Upper Mount Gravatt provides major retail and dining amenity, and the established residential streets of Eight Mile Plains itself provide a pleasant and well-maintained living environment.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The housing stock in Eight Mile Plains includes a mix of established family homes, townhouses, and units that reflect the suburb's dual appeal to owner-occupiers and investors. Properties that present well, are maintained to a standard that supports the tenant demand the suburb attracts, and are correctly positioned in the market relative to recent comparable sales consistently achieve strong results. Sellers who understand that the Eight Mile Plains buyer is often making a calculated, practical decision are better placed to present and price their property in a way that resonates with that mindset.
    </p>
